DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(2,9,1);
$b1 = random(2,9,1);
$c1 = sqrt($b1/$a1);
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the function \( f(x) = $a1 x + $b1 x ^ { -1 } \).
For this function there are three numbers \(A<B<C\) which are either critical
or not in the domain of the function:
$BR
\( A = \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = -$c1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( B = \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = 0;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( C = \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $c1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
For each of the following intervals, tell whether \( f'(x) \)
is positive (type in \(+\)) or negative (type in \(-\)).
$BR
 \( (-\infty, A) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "+";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( (A,B) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "-";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( (B,C) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "-";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( (C,\infty) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "+";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
For each of the numbers \(A\), \(B\), \(C\) state whether it is a local
maximum (type MAX), minimum (type MIN) or not in the domain of \(f(x)\)
(type DNE):
$BR
\(A\): \{ans_rule()\}
$BR
\(B\): \{ans_rule()\}
$BR
\(C\): \{ans_rule()\}
END_TEXT

ANS(str_cmp("MAX"));
ANS(str_cmp("DNE"));
ANS(str_cmp("MIN"));
ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.

